The media fraternity has yet again lost another member. Business Report Deputy Editor Sechaba Ka’Nkosi has been confirmed dead by his close friend and his brother. It is alleged that Ka’Nkosi was found dead at his home this morning after he could not be found for the past three days. His friend Mondli Makhanya said he was found lying on the floor and the cause of death is still unknown. “We have lost a good man, it’s such a shame,” he said. Ka’Nkosi’s brother said they could not give anymore details until tomorrow. Sechaba is known to have has travelled Africa extensively as a correspondent. Some of the publications he worked for are The Guardian which also contributed to the Mail & Guardian. He was also a force at the Sunday Times and was a founding member of the Sunday World newspaper.